Wash and dry all produce. Preheat grill to high (you can skip this if cooking on the stove). Peel @Russet Potato{1}, then cut into ½-inch cubes. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough @water{} to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and add a pinch of @salt{}. Cook until easily pierced by a knife, ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and return to #pot{} to let dry out.

Meanwhile, trim @Scallions{2}(trimmed), then thinly slice on an angle. Cut @Butter{2%tbsp} into a few small pieces. Thinly slice @Celery{1}. Peel, then grate @Carrots{1}. In a #medium bowl{}, toss celery, carrot, @White Wine Vinegar{1%tbsp}, @Celery Salt{1/2%tsp}, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, and a pinch each of @Pepper{} and @Sugar{pinch}.

> We sent more vinegar and celery salt than needed.

If cooking @Chicken Breasts{12%ounce} on the stove, heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat chicken dry with a #paper towel{}, then rub with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Cook in pan or on #grill{} over direct heat until no longer pink in center, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. Remove from pan or grill and set aside.

Add @Frank's Red Hot Sauce{1/4%cup} to same pan you cooked chicken in. (TIP: If grilling, heat the sauce in a small #pot{}.) Bring to a gentle simmer over medium heat, then reduce heat to low. Add @Butter{2%tbsp} one piece at a time, whisking to melt and incorporate. Once all of the butter has been mixed in, add chicken and gently toss to coat. Remove from heat.

Add @Sour Cream{4%tbsp} to drained potato in pot. Mash with a #potato masher{} or #wooden spoon{} until mostly smooth. Stir in half the scallions. Season with salt and pepper.

> If potato has cooled, quickly reheat over medium-low heat.

Divide slaw and mashed potato between #plates{}. Add chicken, allowing excess sauce to drip off before plating. Garnish with remaining scallions and serve.